<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<component xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="racepoint_component_profile.xsd" manufacturer="Panix" model="Sentinel Pro Pro Host" alias="ProHost Sentinel Rubi Bridge v4.3b1-pro" device_class="Generic_component" minimum_component_engine_version="8.4" rpm_xml_version="1.2">
    <notes>ProHost Sentinel Rubi Bridge v4.3b1-pro

Copyright (c) Savant Cyprus 2026
App Microsite: https://savantcyprus.com/sentinel-pro.html
Bridge Microsite: https://savantcyprus.com/sentinel-pro.html

Purpose
- Clean application bridge profile for Savant host.
- Uses benumc/rubi as the runtime console layer.
- Opens an app-facing TCP port for the mobile client backend.

Upstream runtime
- benumc/rubi
- https://github.com/benumc/rubi

Design rules
- no references to prior automation bridges
- app-facing port is configurable in Blueprint
- default app-facing port is 42042
- runtime status is exposed to StateCenter for diagnostics
- bridge auto-starts when the profile loads
- harvest is discovery-oriented instead of fixed to three hard-coded globals
- users_file points to the persistent Sentinel home store on the host filesystem

Version notes
- v4.3b1-pro
- ProHosts profile for modern SavantOS shared-user filesystem layout.
- Keeps live `sclibridge statenames` discovery, batched `readstate`, HTTPS transport, and dual-layout host support.
- Supersedes earlier secure and pre-secure iterations.
</notes>
